    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Mona Lisa Smile': How Different Are Students Today?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Catherine E Doenges letter says that decade of college teaching tells her that in every semester she can reach at least one student</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Take heart, Prof. Rhonda Garelick (''Career Girls,'' Op-Ed, Jan. 24).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Take heart, Prof. Rhonda Garelick (''Career Girls,'' Op-Ed, Jan. 24).</p>
        <p>After more than a decade of college teaching, I have met many an apathetic student. But every semester I always reach someone, sometimes more than one.</p>
        <p>Teach for these people. It takes only one individual to begin a movement.</p>
        <p>CATHERINE E. DOENGES  Fairfield, Conn., Jan. 24, 2004</p>
      </block>
